2 unit(s) Chicken Breasts
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
3 unit(s) Radish
113 g Baby Tomatoes
3 tbsp Guacamole
2 tbsp Ranch Dressing
113 g Spring Mix
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
28 g Seed Blend
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Cut cucumber into 1/4-inch rounds.
Thinly slice radishes.
Halve tomatoes.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat. When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then chicken.
Cook on one side until golden, 6-7 min. Flip, then cover and continue cooking until cooked through, 6-7 min.**

Meanwhile, add guacamole and ranch to a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Heat a small non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add seeds to the dry pan. Toast, stirring often, until golden, 3-4 min. (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn!)
Transfer to a plate.

Thinly slice chicken.
Divide spring mix between plates, then top with tomatoes, cucumbers, radishes and chicken.
Drizzle dressing over salad.
Sprinkle feta and seed blend over top.